<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"><span style="">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>As we can see<b>,</b> two Apostles tell us
that all of Scripture is from God<b>.</b> Therefore<b>,</b> it is </span><u><span
        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman Bold&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;"
        lang="EN-US">not</span></u><span style="font-size: 12pt;" lang="EN-US"> logical to think that different sections of Scripture
teach opposing things<b>,</b> things that oppose one another<b>.</b><span style="">&nbsp; </span><b>God is not a being prone to contradiction,
anarchy, and chaos, but harmony. <u>Therefore, all correct interpretation must
be in harmony with the rest of the Bible</u>.</b> <o:p></o:p></span></p>

